      "lesson title": "AI in Exams and Assessments: Fairness and Integrity",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As AI tools become more common in education, schools and universities are increasingly using AI detection software to identify whether students have used artificial intelligence in their work. However, these detection systems are far from perfect, and they can make serious errors, including falsely accusing honest students of cheating. This lesson explores how AI detection tools work, why they sometimes get things wrong, and what the consequences of those errors can be for students and institutions. We will also look at how some individuals attempt to manipulate or bypass these systems, and why that creates new challenges for maintaining fairness in assessments. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of the limitations of AI detection and what fair, balanced assessment practices might look like in an AI-aware world.",
